<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idf69710ae-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s12308"><num value="12308">§ 12308.</num><heading> Providing vessel numbering and registration information</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">A person may request from an authority issuing a number under this chapter the numbering and registration information of a vessel that is retrievable from vessel numbering system records of the issuing authority. When the issuing authority is satisfied that the request is reasonable and related to a boating safety purpose, the information shall be provided on paying the cost of retrieving and providing the information requested.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idf69710af-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5">(<ref href="/us/pl/98/89">Pub. L. 98–89</ref>, <date date="1983-08-26">Aug. 26, 1983</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/97/592">97 Stat. 592</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
